Usually, after the weather, I am here to tell you about how we have been saved 
from some world-ending danger – that, for whatever reason, has failed again 
to end our world.

But today, I have no such report, because there is no such danger. Or, there is 
an infinitude of such dangers. Rocks hurdling unseen from space, gamma ray 
bursts created by chance and utterly destroying by chance, disease, war, 
hunger, or the slow dissipation of it all – not by the sudden, but by the 
gradual always.

But now is not the time for such light-hearted childish thoughts.
%
